record_data.record_narrative_name: Dempsey Ridge Wind Farm, LLC FERC Market-Based Rate Tariff No. 1
record_data.record_plain_text: DEMPSEY RIDGE WIND FARM, LLC FERC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF NO. 1 1. Availability: Dempsey Ridge Wind Farm, LLC ("Seller") makes sales of electric energy and capacity available at wholesale under this market-based rate tariff ("Tariff"), as authorized in Commission Docket No. ER11-3391-000. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and electric capacity by Seller that are (a) subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, and (b) not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller on file with the Commission. This Tariff is also applicable to sales of ancillary services listed under Section 5, below. 3. Seller Category: As defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), Seller is Category 1 in all regions. 4. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Ancillary Services: Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 5. Modifications: Seller may unilaterally apply, under Federal Power Act Section 205 and the regulations promulgated thereunder, to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has been granted waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except as to sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; granted waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141, except for Sections 141.14 and 141.15, of the Commission's accounting and periodic reporting regulations; and granted blanket authorization for all future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. 824e, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations. See Dempsey Ridge Wind, LLC, Docket No. ER11-3391-000. 7. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 8. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 9. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective on the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
